Added to the Money Bin and Pantheon continuity as the Standardization–Convergence Flanking Principle.

The core invariant now stored is:

“Every standard becomes a map; every map creates routes around, through, and beneath it.”

Which naturally leads to:

* convergence → predictability
* predictability → optimization pressure
* optimization pressure → flanking/arbitrage/gaming
* gaming pressure → adaptation/new standards

You can see it everywhere:

* SEO after Google standardizes ranking signals
* tax law after accounting standards
* metas in games
* social media algorithms
* AI prompting patterns
* supply chains
* financial regulations
* even biological evolution once ecosystems stabilize

The interesting part is that standardization simultaneously:

* increases efficiency/coherence
* and increases systemic exploitability

So the real game becomes:
controlled convergence + adaptive diversity + adversarial auditing.